5:
The merging of worlds with
Pandemonium, while the Abyss
encroaches... Though our fight with
the Lord of Shadow has ended,
another begins.
8:
After we were forced to abandon
our world, my people were left with
no choice but to create a new place
to call home. We pressed on.
11:
We were blessed with reliable allies.
And together, we were to forge
ahead to create a bright new future.
19:
We may have won the battle, but at
what cost? Everything is ruined...
22:
We can rebuild! There is no doubt in
my mind that with our aid, the
people here will find their way once
more.
26:
Your Highness... You mean we will be
the ones to save them?
41:
Another long vacation might do
your troubled heart some good.
46:
Another vacation—before Alk and
the others return? I couldn't possibly.
50:
Mmm, you have a point. It wouldn't
do to have you in a bikini without the
one who would enjoy seeing it the
most.
55:
Must you always attempt to raise
my spirits with such provocative
teasing? Still, I appreciate it, Estel.
59:
So... how will you proceed? Cutting
ties with Palpebra now would be a
great loss for us all.
63:
Indeed. But I plan to do no such
thing.
66:
The most logical course of action
would be to curry favor by offering
our aid.
69:
After all, their defeat would mean
the end of not only this world—but
all worlds as we know it.
73:
Heh, hence the construction of an
ark of salvation to pass between
worlds. Brilliantly foolish, or foolishly
brilliant, I cannot tell.
77:
Still, I cannot deny that our power is
a shadow of what it once was.
80:
Our forces were decimated in the
fight against the Purgers. Many of
my people lost everything—their
homes and all those they held dear.
83:
They look to me for guidance. And
thus, it falls to me to decide our path
forward.
87:
Shakari's last words to me were that
I am free to do with my life as I wish.
And I will not take that freedom for
granted.
91:
I see that your mind is already
made up. The noble heart of a
knight, through and through...
94:
Then let us be off, King of Man! I shall
have some more fitting garments
prepared for you at once!
102:
The flame you hold is a beacon of
hope for our people. You must also
look the part.
113: Princess Lilith, I beg of you.
115:
Allow us to fly to the aid of our allies!
Just say the word, and we shall
make it so!
121:
I must admit... I was fully opposed to
this course of action at first.
123:
However, if we do not act to defend
our allies, one day there will be no
one left to protect us.
125:
We know firsthand what it means to
endure the long dark. But that is
precisely why we must become the
light of hope for them.
132:
It looks like the others are ready and
raring to go. Do allow me to tag
along.
135:
If we must go, we wish to go at your
behest! So please, my lady—give us
your command!
143:
Thank you... It is because of you all
that my flame of hope still burns
bright.
146:
I, Lilith Stratos, hereby command
you, brave knights.
150: Save our allies at any cost!
156:
Pur Lilie, I shall leave the rest of the
details of their deployment to you.
160: Y-yes, ma'am! I won't let you down!
163:
And, er... I don't mean to sound
ungrateful for your help, but... why
leave me in charge?
167:
Because you and I are of the same
mind.
175:
The flames of our people cannot be
protected without the means to do
so. Hence, a government is nothing
without organization.
178:
So I thought to myself, who here is
responsible for the structure that
holds Palpebra together?
181:
When I asked Alk and the others for
their advice, they all named the
same person. And that person is you.
185:
H-huh? I'm nothing special, really!
To be honest, Keira and Sharon
would be much better—
188:
The two of them sang your praises
as well.
197:
So if you are willing to share, I wish
to know more about your methods.
200:
About the hardships you have
endured thus far... and the
challenges yet to come.
204:
That I may better lighten your
burden.
212:
Yup, you're right... A problem shared
is a problem halved!
216:
With your help, we'll be back on our
feet in no time. And my approval
ratings will be through the roof!
220:
Ah, just as everyone said. You are
quite motivated by approval.
225:
Wha—cut it out, princess! No need to
air out ALL of my dirty laundry!
230:
I may be a bit of a troublemaker, but
I'll try my best to follow in your
footsteps, Lilie!
